events.938: City of Youzhou established during the Later Jin dynasty.
events.1153: Jurchen Jin dynasty moves capital to present-day Beijing.
events.1215: Khubilai Khan establishes Yuan dynasty and makes Dadu (present-day Beijing) the capital.
events.1368: Ming dynasty moves capital to present-day Beijing and renames it Beijing ('Northern Capital').
events.1406: Construction of the Forbidden City begins under the Ming dynasty.
events.1420: Beijing becomes the capital of the Ming dynasty.
events.1644: Manchu Qing dynasty captures Beijing and makes it their capital.
events.1860: Anglo-French forces capture Beijing during the Second Opium War.
events.1912: Republic of China established with Beijing as its capital.
events.1949: People's Republic of China established with Beijing as its capital.
events.1958: Great Leap Forward campaign leads to significant social and economic changes in Beijing.
events.1966: Cultural Revolution impacts Beijing, leading to widespread social and political upheaval.
events.1989: Tiananmen Square protests and subsequent military crackdown.
events.2022: Ongoing modernization and urban development continue to shape the city of Beijing.
events.-1045: First recorded settlement in area of present-day Beijing.
events.-221: City of Ji becomes a regional capital during the Qin dynasty.
